<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>FAQ & Help - Zoofi</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #444;
      }
      .faq {
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      label {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 10px;
      }
      input,
      textarea {
        width: 100%;
        padding: 8px;
        margin-top: 5px;
      }
      button {
        margin-top: 10px;
        padding: 10px 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>FAQ & Help</h1>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>What is Zoofi?</h2>
      <p>
        Zoofi is a meme NFT platform where users can mint, explore, and trade
        viral memes as NFTs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>How do I mint a meme?</h2>
      <p>
        Go to the <a href="/mint">/mint</a> page, fill in the meme details, and
        hit Mint. Make sure your wallet is connected.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>Do I need crypto to mint?</h2>
      <p>
        Yes, minting requires a small fee in crypto depending on the network
        youâ€™re using (e.g., Sui, Ethereum).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>Can I sell my meme?</h2>
      <p>
        Yes! Once minted, you can list your meme for sale and others can buy it
        from the explore page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Need more help? Contact us:</h2>
    <form method="POST" action="/contact">
      <label for="email">Your Email</label>
      <input type="email" name="email" id="email" required />

      <label for="message">Your Question / Issue</label>
      <textarea name="message" id="message" rows="4" required></textarea>

      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  </body>
</html>
